 0696: 
 0697:         Steps in the direction given by the direction generator set by
 0698:         set_aim_assister, which has to be called in advance. Otherwise,
 0699:         a RuntimeError is raised.
 0700: 
 0701:         param: t --   Current (pseudo-)time level
 0702:         param: pos -- Current (Cartesian) coordinates, as a three-component
 0703:                       C-contiguous NumPy array
 0704:         param: h --   Current time increment
 0705: 
 0706:         return: t --   (a) New (pseudo-)time level, if the attempted step is
 0707:                            accepted
 0708:                        (b) Current (pseudo-)time level, if the attempted step is
 0709:                            rejected
 0710:         return: pos -- Three-component C-contiguous NumPy array, containing
 0711:                        (a) Dormand-Prince 5(4) Bspline approximation of the
 0712:                            (Cartesian) coordinates at the new time level, if the
 0713:                            attempted step is accepted
 0714:                        (b) Current (Cartesian) coordinates; unaltered, if the
 0715:                            attempted step is rejected
 0716:         return: h --   Updated (pseudo-)time increment. Generally increased
 0717:                        or decreased, depending on whether or not the trial step
 0718:                        is accepted.

 1480:         """Dp87Linear.__call__(t,pos,h)
 1481: 
 1482:         Attempts a single step forwards in (pseudo-)time, using the
 1483:         Dormand-Prince 8(7) adaptive integrator scheme. If the attempted step
 1484:         is rejected, the time level and coordinates are not updated, while the
 1485:         time increment is refined.
 1486: 
 1487:         Steps in the direction given by the direction generator set by
 1488:         set_aim_assister, which has to be called in advance. Otherwise,
 1489:         a RuntimeError is raised.
 1490: 
 1491:         param: t --   Current (pseudo-)time level
 1492:         param: pos -- Current (Cartesian) coordinates, as a three-component
 1493:                       C-contiguous NumPy array
 1494:         param: h --   Current time increment
 1495: 
 1496:         return: t --   (a) New (pseudo-)time level, if the attempted step is
 1497:                            accepted
 1498:                        (b) Current (pseudo-)time level, if the attempted step is
 1499:                            rejected
 1500:         return: pos -- Three-component C-contiguous NumPy array, containing
 1501:                        (a) Dormand-Prince 8(7) Bspline approximation of the
 1502:                            (Cartesian) coordinates at the new time level, if the
 1503:                            attempted step is accepted
 1504:                        (b) Current (Cartesian) coordinates; unaltered, if the
 1505:                            attempted step is rejected
 1506:         return: h --   Updated (pseudo-)time increment. Generally increased
 1507:                        or decreased, depending on whether or not the trial step
 1508:                        is accepted.
